The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Card sop for Bihar farmers
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Card sop for Bihar farmers
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, Nov. 27: In a measure aimed at breaking the nexus between middlemen and governments grain purchase centres, the Bihar government has decided to issue identity cards to farmers.        
	Besides, the farmers will also get land health card.        
	Farmers in possession of identity card can sell their produce directly at the purchase centres without involvement of scores of middlemen.        
	Food and civil supplies secretary Tripurari Sharan has written a letter to all the district magistrates directing them to issue identity cards to all the farmers.         
	The land health card will contain the details of a lands fertility and also suggestions about what should be grown on particular land.                                
	The government had launched a drive to enable the farmers get soil examined by agriculture experts last year. But the drive failed for the farmers did not respond properly. Now the government has taken on its own to test soil in rural areas.         
	Sources in the agriculture department revealed that the experts would collect two samples each from 44,925 villages across the state. Subsequently, all the 89,850 samples will be examined at the centres set up at block and district headquarters.        
	Agriculture department deputy director A.C. Jain said that the unemployed agriculture graduates and retired agriculture experts would be engaged in the exercise daily. They will be paid Rs 250 per day for collecting samples and testing them at the labs.                                                                                                                                                          
